  <h2>Adding Headers and Footers</h2>

  <p>
    Professional documents often need headers and footers with page numbers,
    dates, or company logos.
  </p>

  <pre><code class="language-json">&#123;
  "url": "https://example.com/report",
  "format": "A4",
  "displayHeaderFooter": true,
  "headerTemplate": "&lt;div style='font-size:10px; text-align:center; width:100%;'&gt;Company Name - Confidential&lt;/div&gt;",
  "footerTemplate": "&lt;div style='font-size:10px; text-align:center; width:100%;'&gt;Page &lt;span class='pageNumber'&gt;&lt;/span&gt; of &lt;span class='totalPages'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
  "margin": &#123;
    "top": "100px",
    "bottom": "80px",
    "left": "40px",
    "right": "40px"
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <p>
    Available template variables:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><code>pageNumber</code> - Current page number</li>
    <li><code>totalPages</code> - Total number of pages</li>
    <li><code>date</code> - Current date</li>
    <li><code>title</code> - Document title</li>
    <li><code>url</code> - Source URL</li>
  </ul>

